<Layout title="Divorce Professionals · Florida Divorce + Real Estate Partner Hub — Family Law Attorneys, Mediators, CDFAs, Forensic Accountants &amp; Marital Home Buyout Refinance Coordination" description="Florida divorce professional partner hub educating divorcing parties on what the divorce team does in real estate transactions: equitable distribution analysis under Florida Statutes Chapter 61.075 starting from presumption of equal distribution then adjusting for statutory factors including contribution to marriage and economic circumstances and marriage duration and interruption of personal careers and contributions to other spouse's career and intentional dissipation; marital vs non-marital property classification with premarital assets and gifts and inheritances to one spouse and assets traceable to non-marital sources remaining non-marital; marital home valuation through USPAP-licensed real estate appraisers commonly joint or dueling appraisals; business interest valuation through CPA forensic accountants with ABV Accredited in Business Valuation or CFF Certified in Financial Forensics credentials through AICPA applying Income Market and Asset approaches; Marital Settlement Agreement MSA drafting with property division terms aligned with refinance closing timeline; court-ordered mediation in many Florida judicial circuits through Florida Supreme Court certified family mediators; alimony and child support income projections via Certified Divorce Financial Analyst CDFA through Institute for Divorce Financial Analysts; retirement plan division through Qualified Domestic Relations Order QDRO preparation by ERISA-qualified attorney for 401k and pension division under IRC Section 414(p); marital home buyout cash-out refinance with the keeping spouse qualified on W-2 plus alimony plus child support per Fannie Mae B3-3.1-09 with 3+ year continuance requirement; post-judgment quitclaim deed timing aligned with refinance closing; and TCJA Tax Cuts and Jobs Act effective January 1 2019 elimination of alimony deduction for payors and inclusion in payee's income for divorces finalized after 2018. Five divorce professional types: family law attorney as primary divorce counsel with Florida Bar Family Law Section membership handling dissolution petition and discovery and MSA drafting and court representation; family mediator as Florida Supreme Court certified facilitator of settlement negotiation; Certified Divorce Financial Analyst CDFA credentialed through Institute for Divorce Financial Analysts for property division scenario modeling and cash flow analysis; forensic accountant CPA with ABV or CFF credentials for business interest valuation and lifestyle analysis and hidden asset investigation; USPAP-certified real estate appraiser for marital home valuation. Florida alimony reform: 2023 SB 1416 modified durational alimony provisions and eliminated permanent alimony as standard type. Partner-as-borrower CTA routing divorce professionals to /professional-services/ hub for multi-source income mortgage qualifying paths covering W-2 + partnership K-1 + variable bonus + book-of-business under Fannie Mae B3-3.1-01 and B3-3.4-02 documentation." canonical="https://stairwaymortgage.com/divorce-professionals/">
  <div class="pdivorce-scope" set:html={pdivorceBody} />
</Layout>

